# Pre-requisites Setup Completed

**The following tools and services were verified before starting the MedTrack Cloud-Enabled Healthcare Management System project:**

1. AWS Account

Successfully created and logged into the AWS Management Console to manage all cloud resources required for the project.

2. AWS IAM

Access to AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) was verified to manage roles, policies, and permissions for secure access to AWS services.

3. AWS EC2

Access to the Amazon EC2 service was confirmed to host and deploy the Flask-based MedTrack application.

4. AWS DynamoDB

Verified the availability of Amazon DynamoDB to store healthcare data such as patient records, doctor information, and appointment details using a NoSQL database.

5. Development Environment

Installed and configured the following development tools:

• Python – used for backend development with Flask
• Git – used for version control and project management
• Visual Studio Code – used as the code editor for application development

Conclusion

These prerequisites ensure the development environment is properly configured for building and deploying the MedTrack Cloud-Based Healthcare Management System.